<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Don't ask for dolphins at JJ's place
 &HT;    By Cheryl Blackerby
 &HT;    c. 1998 Palm Beach Post/Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI BEACH, Fla. _ Want to watch a game and eat at the same
time?
</P>
<P>
   How about a lot of games?
</P>
<P>
   At Miami Dolphins Coach Jimmy Johnson's restaurant,
coincidentally called Jimmy Johnson's Three Rings Bar and Grill,
you can watch all the sports you want on 35 TVs.
</P>
<P>
   At Jimmy's, don't look for dolphin on the menu (the name has
been changed to mahi-mahi) but you can get the Brent Burger ($7.25)
and the Chad Chicken Sandwich ($8.25), named after Johnson's sons,
and the Rhonda Pasta Primavera ($10.50), inspired by Johnson's
girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
   Jimmy chose the nachos as his namesake - Jimmy's Super Nachos
($8.25).
</P>
<P>
   Pictures of Jimmy are all over the place, and if you get tired
of looking at him you can always check out the ocean - the
restaurant is next to the beach - or watch people jumping into a
pool, unaware that there is see-through glass between the pool and
restaurant. (Make sure you don't lose your swimsuit in this pool.)
</P>
<P>
   JJ's is behind the Eden Roc Hotel. It's open from 11:30 a.m. to
2 a.m. and until 4 a.m. Friday and Saturday nights. Call
305-672-6224.
</P>
<P>
   Get there early for a seat to watch a big game, especially a
Dolphins game.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
