<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDENROC-SPA27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eden Roc caters to the rich, famous
 &HT;    By Cheryl Blackerby
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI BEACH, Fla. Women aren't shy in the locker room of the
Eden Roc Spa.
</P>
<P>
   Everyone is walking around naked, their toned and pumped bodies
dripping with sweat. They all look like Linda Hamilton in the movie
Terminator 2: Judgment Day - bulging forearms, ropy thighs and
washboard stomachs.
</P>
<P>
   People get massages here after they've climbed the rock wall
(ropes are attached to your waist in case you fall), and after
they've worked out on the weight machines, and after a ``spinning
class,'' where you ride a bike as if you're doing the last
kilometer in the Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
   You go to this spa if you're feeling strong.
</P>
<P>
   You train like Evander Holyfield in ``box aerobics.'' Then
there's ``power flex,'' an intense 90-minute cardio and strength
training workout designed to keep your heart rate in ``The Zone'';
``step plus,'' a cardio workout that includes step choreography and
abdominal training; and ``aqua challenge,'' water exercises that
would challenge a porpoise.
</P>
<P>
   At this spa, yoga becomes ``power yoga.''
</P>
<P>
   Are you tired just reading this?
</P>
<P>
   Well, you can go to the spa and do none of the above. I went for
a ``deep tissue'' massage, and it was the most relaxing experience
I've had at a resort spa, and I've been to quite a few.
</P>
<P>
   Candlelight, soft music with the sound of a waterfall and birds,
and a massage therapist named Lisa who took an intense massage to
the edge of pain. It felt great, and the manipulation of muscles
and bones left my shoulders and neck feeling mobile and relaxed. I
could turn my head much easier - I hadn't noticed how stiff my neck
was - which made it easier to look for celebs.
</P>
<P>
   I had just missed Neve Campbell and David Lee Roth climbing the
rock wall. Vanessa Williams and Whitney Houston recently got
massages and facials.
</P>
<P>
   I'll come here again. But I'll probably skip the ``step
challenge'' class and go right to the massage rooms.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
