<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ It took the end of the Cold War for
the Senate to debate and approve the expansion of the NATO security
umbrella to Eastern Europe. It will take the end of the debate over
federal budget deficits for the Congress to approve Social Security
reform. (Glass, Cox News Service) MOVED 6/25.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The Supreme Court continues to hold, contrary to
the declared position of the state's governor, that the
Constitution applies to Alabama. The ruling ought to put paid to
the school-prayer hustle, but then so should have all the other
like rulings since 1963. (Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED 6/25.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ In the southern Brazilian town of Bocaiuva do
Sul, the mayor is using Viagra as a key ingredient for
participation in Brazil's formulized revenue sharing. The jokes
keep coming. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED 6/25.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ Best Fourth of July I remember is the only
Fourth of July I remember crying. It was 1990. I was in Moscow.
(Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED 6/25.
</P>
<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ ``We might have a better marriage under the
Southern Baptist plan,'' my wife said one morning. ``If you mean
the deal about wives being graciously submissive to their husbands,
I agree,'' I said. ``I'm willing to give it a try,'' she said.
(Minter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ This concerns a cat and a religious experience.
(Borders, Lufkin Daily News) MOVED.
