   LIFESTYLE (l category)
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ Planning is a wonderful thing in most
endeavors, and no less so in woodworking and furnituremaking. One
simply does not embark on a project before deciding how everything
is going to be done, and when it is going to be done. A project's
dimensions, among other things, are predicated upon the joinery.
(Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HARLEY-MINISTER _ PALM BEACH GARDENS, Fla. _ The Rev. Ray
Underwood is a 6-foot-5, 200-pound, 39-year-old pastor with a high
energy style who rides a ``hog,'' a Harley-Davidson motorcycle, to
services at the church he founded 13 years ago. Now, this wired
pastor pours his daring and enthusiasm into his work. The Palm
Beach Community Church in Palm Beach Gardens that frequently draws
as many as 1,000 people on a Sunday is, not surprisingly, a
different kind of place. (Gushee, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e category)
</P>
<P>
   GWTW-ART _ For years, artist Armand Seguso's descendants have
been looking for his art, which was used in the original poster and
programs for the movie ``Gone With the Wind.'' Grandson Rick Seguso
thinks MGM's art department may have simply discarded or misplaced
the oils. But Armand Seguso owned the rights to the original works,
his grandson said. It's possible he might have painted over the
canvases, or thrown them out himself. (Schwan, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   CARDINAL _ In 1993, Cardinal Joseph Bernardin made international
headlines when he was accused of sexual abuse. During the months
that followed, he faced the accusation, which proved to be false,
with a dignity and grace that brought him the admiration of
millions. Three years later he faced his own death from pancreatic
cancer with the same serenity. On July 7, PBS will air a
documentary on Bernardin. This understated but powerful documentary
includes insights from writers, theologians, and the family and
friends of Bernardin. (Blake, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE (a and/or l category)
</P>
<P>
   ARTHRITIS-DRUG _ WEST PALM BEACH _ Rheumatoid arthritis began
crippling Peter Looram when he was 41. Because the drugs he was
taking weren't working, Looram's doctor recommended an experimental
drug being tested in his area. In a remarkably short time after he
started Enbrel _ three weeks _ he was feeling improvement. Pain
decreased, and the ability to move his joints increased. (Susman,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SPRINGS-CLEANING _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Mayor Kirk Watson, showing
off Barton Springs Pool's first cleaning in five weeks, outlined
what he hoped would become a permanent solution to the conflict
over the endangered species and the preservation of a spring-fed
swimming pool that has taken on iconic proportions for many Central
Texans. (Copelin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-PONTEVEDRA _ PONTE VEDRA, Fla. _ There wasn't exactly
gold in them thar hills. In fact, there weren't even any hills.
Just a lot of sand next to the ocean. But there were rich veins of
rutile, ilmenite and zirconium, used in steel processing, and
before you could say ``zirconium rush'' a bustling settlement known
as Mineral City sprang up in the late 1800s in the northeast corner
of Florida. (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
