<P>
   TRAVEL-MIAMIBEACH _ MIAMI BEACH, Fla. _ While you're eating
roast pork at Gloria Estefan's restaurant, Larios, on Ocean Drive,
you can impress your friends with your knowledge of Art Deco. All
you really need to know is this: The Art Deco buildings in Miami
Beach had three influences - cruise ships, the French world
exposition in 1926 and the turn-of-the-century German philosophy of
no frills architecture. (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MIAMIBEACH-JJ. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-MERRITISLE _ MERRITT ISLAND, Fla. _ A space center and a
scenic refuge live next door here, co-existing as friendly
neighbors. In fact, Merritt Island National Wildlife Refuge began
as a buffer zone for Cape Canaveral, when the National Aeronautical
and Space Administration bought 88,000 acres of Merritt Island in
1963. Now, people come here to see the birds, manatees, bobcats and
raccoons. (Lopinot, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
