scenic refuge live next door here, co-existing as friendly
neighbors. In fact, Merritt Island National Wildlife Refuge began
as a buffer zone for Cape Canaveral, when the National Aeronautical
and Space Administration bought 88,000 acres of Merritt Island in
1963. Now, people come here to see the birds, manatees, bobcats and
raccoons. (Lopinot, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
