   SF-AIR (San Francisco) _ The U.S. Environmental Protection
Agency punished the Bay Area on by taking away its coveted
clear-air status, leaving nine counties vulnerable to tougher curbs
on cars, factories and households. By JANE KAY.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ACTING-VOICES (Undated) _ These days, a lot of bad voices are
making a lot of good money. ``Talent and training often have
nothing to do with (an actor's) work, because casting is done
cosmetically,'' said James Spruill, an associate professor of
theater at Boston University. ``The most important thing is `the
look.''' By AMY BIANCOLLI. (For release Sunday, June 28.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-SIGHT (Undated) _ ``Out of Sight'' is, like the
terrific ``Get Shorty,'' based on an Elmore Leonard novel and
produced by Jersey Films. This time, that teaming-up gave birth to
a sad and deflated follow-up. By BARBARA SHULGASSER.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-INSOMNIAC (Undated) _ Wrtier-director Tiffanie
DeBartolo's film debut is the admirable ``Dream for an Insomniac.''
Set in San Francisco (her father is 49ers owner Eddie), the story
concerns an aspiring actress named Francesca (Ione Skye), who is
planning to move to Los Angeles in 48 hours. By BARBARA SHULGASSER.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-WIND (Undated) _ Fifty-nine years after ``Gone with
the Wind'' was first released, this grand old dame of American film
is too plump with its own significance to be judged by modern eyes.
Too much time has passed since its premiere, too much history, too
much celluloid, too many thunderous shifts in pop culture and
society. Acting has changed. By AMY BIANCOLLI.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-HEAVEN (Undated) _ ``Under Heaven'' is ``The Wings
of the Dove'' set in late 20th century America. As the Henry James
novel has already been filmed as is, it is easy to see how
something in writer-director Meg Richman's re-conception has let
the air seep out of a pretty sexy idea. By BARBARA SHULGASSER.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-DOLITTLE (Undated) _ Buried somewhere deep inside
the Eddie Murphy vehicle ``Dr. Dolittle'' is a nice little family
movie about a successful, driven dad who finally gets in touch with
the warm and fuzzy things in life. By WALTER ADDIEGO.
</P>
