<HEADER>
A8558 &Cx1f; tth-z
r v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-FEATURE-SPI &LR;      06-26 0180
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-FEATURE-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, June 27, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   WORKPLACE-COLUMN-SMITH (Undated) Your boss getting on your
nerves? Work driving you up a wall? Try petting a puppy. On several
occasions, a Seattle P-I employee has brought a batch of English
Cocker Spaniel pups to work, and the reaction has been both swift
and amusing.
</P>
<P>
   By Carol Smith. (story will move in the ``f'' category)
</P>
