   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-CLINTON _ BEIJING _ Clinton accepts 21-Gun Salute in
Tiananmen Square. (Albright, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   With CHINA-COMPOUND-$ADV27 _ BEIJING _ Chinese artisans have
been renovating a secluded waterside pavilion inside the communist
leadership compound where President Bill Clinton is expected to
hold some of his most sensitive talks. The 213-acre complex called
Zhongnanhai has no equivalent in America. It is a Beijing-style
amalgam of the White House, Camp David, parts of Georgetown and an
incumbent president's national party headquarters. (Kunstel, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   With CHINA-HISTBOX-$ADV27 _ Tiananmen Square Has Crucial Role
Throughout Chinese History. (Albright, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Sidebars MOVED Wednesday, June 24.
</P>
<P>
   JOURNAL-LITHUANIA _ VILNIUS, Lithuania _ It is a grim,
frightfully intimate job performed by Juozas Aleksiejunas. He gives
guided tours of his former hell. The 76-year-old Aleksiejunas
escorts visitors around Lithuania's appallingly well-preserved KGB
prison, a lingering monument to the bleak, brutal days of the
Soviet Union. ``I felt ill when I came back here,'' he said of his
first glimpse of the prison in 1992, almost 50 years after his
incarceration. (Holmes). EDs: MOVED Tuesday, June 23 in both the
(i) International and (k) Commentary categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-CHICANOS _ MEXICO CITY _ The National Association for
Chicano and Chicana Studies holds a conference in Mexico City for
the first time, bringing together people on both sides of the
border who are linked by heritage yet often mutually misunderstood.
(Ferriss, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Thursday, June 25.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   FUTURE-COURT _ WASHINGTON _ The most coveted room in U.S.
District Court is booked solid until February. Welcome to Courtroom
No. 9, one of 10 of the nation's federal ``electronic courtrooms,''
with equipment that improves the presentation of evidence.
(Abulhassan, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-2000 _ FAIRFAX, Va. _ American prosperity could be
eroded by slow progress in many other countries toward updating
millions of computer systems and billions of microchips to
recognize the year 2000. (Mollison, Cox News Service 630&AMP;add).
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTERS-DATA _ How much fixing the Y2K bug will cost worldwide
and how much has been spent so far. (100 words).
</P>
<P>
   Both MOVED Thursday in advance in (w) Washington and (f)
financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   FEDBUD-SURPLUS _ WASHINGTON _ After a three-decade struggle that
included a national crusade to add a balanced-budget amendment to
the U.S. Constitution, the federal deficit monster has morphed into
a budget surplus. (Malone, Cox News Service 880).
</P>
<P>
   FEDBUD-DATA _ How trust fund income masks the size of the budget
deficit. (100 words). Both MOVED Thursday in advance.
