THIS WEEK'S BUSINESS EVENTS CALENDAR  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, JUNE 28) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONDAY: The Agriculture Department reports on May farm prices
and on crop conditions for wheat, corn, soybeans and cotton.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY: The Federal Reserve's policy-setting Federal Open
Market Committee begins its two-day meeting on interest rates. No
policy shift is expected.
</P>
<P>
   The Conference Board releases its consumer confidence index for
June. The forecast is for an increase of 0.1 point, to 135.3.
</P>
<P>
   Mitsubishi Bank/Schroder Wertheim releases its weekly retail
sales report.
</P>
<P>
   LJR Redbook Research releases its weekly retail sales survey.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY: The Conference Board reports on the leading economic
indicators for May. No change is foreseen.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on construction spending for
May. An increase of 0.2 percent is expected.
</P>
<P>
   The National Association of Purchasing Management releases its
June purchasing managers' index. A drop of 0.1, to 51.3, is
expected.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY: The Commerce Department reports on factory orders for
May. The average forecast is for a decrease of 0.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The Labor Department releases the employment report for June. No
change is expected in the unemployment rate, now at 4.3 percent.
The department also reports on weekly claims for unemployment
insurance.
</P>
