<SLUG> BC-HOT-TIPS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`BAYWATCH' HUNK SAYS `SLIP! SLOP! SLAP!'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BARBARA DE WITT 
c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; It's summer _ and time to fry your skin in the
name of fashion. But before you butter your bod, listen up.
According to hunky ``Baywatch'' star Jose Solano, you're supposed
to ``Slip! Slop! Slap!''
</P>
<P>
   Solano, the new spokesman for the American Cancer Society Skin
Protection Federation, is asking sun worshipers to slip on a shirt,
slop on sunscreen (SPF 15 and higher) and slap on a hat. He also
suggests avoiding the midday sun _ it's the most damaging to your
skin.
</P>
<P>
   Now, if you want to fake it, try Origins Summer Vacation, the
all-natural cosmetic company's first fake tanning cream, priced at
$17.50. It gives a golden glow on darker complexions but looks a
tad fake (dark) on pale ``Snow White'' skin. And for that
sun-streaked look in your hair without bleach, Origins has
introduced Change Your Locks hair-streaking sticks in such colors
as Golden, Honey and Bronze, priced at $14. Miz Hot Tips discovered
it's not a mascara wand but a giant pencil that you get wet and
glide directly onto the hair and it stays put until you wash it
out. It's cool.
</P>
<P>
   While you're working on your tan (fake or otherwise), you'll
have time to read something that requires no brain power, since
it's mostly pictures. It's ``The Brewer Twins: Double Take''
(Universe; $17.95) by Derek and Keith Brewer, the Redondo Beach
surfer boys who became supermodels.
</P>
<P>
   FORGET STARBUCKS: Hate spending big bucks for the taste of
lattes to linger on your lips? The Bare Escentuals shops (there's
one at Topanga Plaza in Canoga Park), have a nifty idea called Buzz
Latte for Lips. It's a sheer gloss that smells and tastes like
coffee, because it's made with real coffee, priced at $12.
</P>
<P>
   If you just want the look of iced mocha, with vitamins A and E
added to soothe dry lips, try Trucco's new Ice Queen by Trucco (a
division of Sebastian International), priced at $6.50.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE DOWN SIDE: Maybe you've been buzzing all day at the
office, and what you're really looking for is a luxurious downer.
To chase the office demons out of your mind, try Bare Escentuals'
new Peace and Quiet foaming bath and body balm for $10. Miz Hot
Tips soaked in it and found it swell, especially with soft violin
music and a glass of valpolicella. But that's up to you.
</P>
<P>
   An alternative is Connie Stevens' new executive day spa and
boutique called the Garden Sanctuary, which opens today at 426 S.
Robertson Blvd., Los Angeles. The bubbly singer-actress from the
'60s and '70s (and mom of actress Joely Fisher) has done so well in
the cosmetics business on the Home Shopping Network that she
decided to have her own place, offering relaxing herbal and
aromatherapy body wraps and massages, fake tan applications and
reflexology treatments. The number is (310) 288-3024.
</P>
<P>
   BABE WATCH: So, you've mowed the lawn and scrubbed the toilets.
Now you're ready for some fun at the mall? Take note that the Fresh
Faces Model Search begins at noon today at Bloomingdale's in the
Beverly Center, and the celebrity judges are Channon Roe of ``Can't
Hardly Wait'' and Jason Young of ``The Bold and the Beautiful.''
Winners receive a modeling contract with L.A. Models Agency and
gifts from Bloomingdale's.
</P>
<P>
   KIDDIE FUN: Does your little angel have a birthday coming up?
Songs such as ``Pool Party'' and ``Pinata Party'' will liven things
up, and you'll find them included in the new CD release ``You're
Invited to Mary Kate &AMP; Ashley's Birthday Party.'' It's about $16 at
the usual music outlets.
</P>
</TEXT>
