morning mist. It hangs in the air, on clothes. It sears the eyes
and throat. Horses in paddocks shake their heads and stomp and pace
skittishly in the gritty gloom. ``The whole county's burning,''
says one of the three firefighters. (Reid, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
