<SLUG> BC-ROUND-ROCK-LEAGUE26-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Reid Ryan to fans: Get on the bus
 &HT;    By Christian Davenport
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROUND ROCK, Texas _ Want to be one of the first to jump on the
Round Rock baseball team bandwagon?
</P>
<P>
   Reid Ryan, son of the legendary pitcher Nolan Ryan, is
organizing a bus trip to San Antonio so eager Central Texas
baseball fans can meet the minor league team he recently bought
with his father and Houston business partner Don Sanders.
</P>
<P>
   They plan to move the Jackson Generals, a Double-A affiliate of
the Houston Astros, to Round Rock for the 2000 baseball season.
</P>
<P>
   Recently, Reid Ryan said that for $25, fans will get a ticket to
the July 16 game between the Generals and the San Antonio Missions,
a round-trip bus ride and all the hot dogs and hamburgers they can
eat. Fans will get a chance before the game to meet the team that
will eventually play in a yet-to-be built stadium on U.S. 79.
</P>
<P>
   Buses will leave the Round Rock Chamber of Commerce, located at
212 East Main St., at 3:30 p.m., July 16. For more information,
call the Chamber at 255-5805.
</P>
<P>
   Buses will also leave from a downtown Austin site that has not
yet been determined. For information on making the trip from
Austin, call 322-5621.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is going to be a great Central Texas rivalry,'' Reid Ryan
said, referring to competition that he said will blossom between
San Antonio and Round Rock.
</P>
<P>
   Reid Ryan has said he also has plans to build a museum for Texas
baseball at the new stadium and a Texas League Hall of Fame.
</P>
<P>
   But the next step, he said, is a name-the-team contest, which is
expected to take place the first week of July.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
