</P>
<P>
   MARLINS-COLUMN _ Picture this. Or better, listen to the distant,
rumbling possibility. We're talking Mark McGwire, baseball's answer
to King Kong, marching into Pro Player Stadium ahead of an army of
satellite TV trucks and a squadron of news helicopters with the
unstated but undeniable goal of erasing Roger Maris' asterisk once
and for all. (Graziano, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MARLINS-GUIDRY _ Joe Fontenot was a year old in 1978, when Ron
Guidry was a New York Yankees hero, pitching hundreds of miles away
from Fontenot's Louisiana hometown of Lafayette. Fontenot was 18 in
1995 when he was drafted by the San Francisco Giants and went off
to play professional baseball. Guidry's nephew, Brooks Badeaux, was
a teammate of Fontenot's at Acadiana High School, just outside of
Lafayette. So when Fontenot's parents called Guidry and asked if
he'd talk with their son about life in pro baseball, Guidry was
happy to help. (Graziano, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DOLPHINS _ RIVIERA BEACH, Fla. _ If ever there has been occasion
for Dwight Stephenson to finally show a vain side, this was it. His
bust: the bronze likeness of the former Miami Dolphins center to be
displayed for perpetuity at the Pro Football Hall of Fame in
Canton, Ohio. (Skolnick, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PANTHERS-DRAFT _ BUFFALO, N.Y. _ Florida has no first-round pick
in the NHL draft, but that doesn't mean the Panthers won't have a
busy weekend.
</P>
<P>
   General Manager Bryan Murray has been negotiating with Nashville
GM David Poile in an effort to land a top goaltending prospect this
afternoon. (Biggane, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
