<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Saturday, June 27 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   WINDOWS98-REVIEW (Los Angeles) _ Call it the Pretty Good
Upgrade. But unless you have new hardware or really love Internet
Explorer 4.0, do you really need to spend $100 or more to upgrade
your computer to Windows 98? Probably not. By David Bloom. (Will
also move in the ``n'' California news file and ``a'' national news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-SCHOOLHOUSE (Los Angeles) _ ``The check is in the mail;
it ought to be there Thursday without fail.'' Disney makes a foray
into the world of financial advising, with the release of ``Money
Rock,'' a home video primer for kids with seven songs covering
banks, checking accounts, Wall Street, taxes and barter. By Dave
McNary.
</P>
