(lb) 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOR SATURDAY AMs
</P>
<P>
   Business Day Front Page (coded ``f'' unless otherwise noted): &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-MERGE (Tokyo) _ Long-Term Credit Bank, one of Japan's
biggest and weakest financial institutions, is in negotiations to
merge with a smaller, stronger rival, a move that could turn the
combined bank into a showcase for the government's first blueprint
to clean up the nation's bad debt. By Sheryl WuDunn.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Display)
</P>
<P>
   SHIPWRECK-SALVAGE (Key West, Fla.) _ A wave of heightened
environmental, cultural and historical concern, along with public
dismay at private gain from drowned antiquities, is crashing into
the old-time practice of shipwreck salvage. By Jim Carrier.
</P>
