<P>
   CHINA-SUMMIT (Beijing) _ President Clinton was formally received
by President Jiang Zemin on Saturday in a military ceremony on
Tiananmen Square, the vast tombstone of a failed revolution. He
stood mute throughout, as is customary at such arrival ceremonies.
Clinton and Jiang then inspected army troops and reviewed an honor
guard on ground that human rights advocates around the world
consider stained with the blood of martyrs. By John M. Broder.
</P>
