   KOSOVO (Pristina, Serbia) _ Belgrade has ordered its military
and special police to mount widescale attacks in Kosovo to
recapture pockets held by ethnic Albanian rebels and reopen roads
the separatist rebels have blocked for weeks, Western diplomats and
military officials said on Friday. The escalation of the fight
against the rebels came as Richard Holbrooke, the U.S. special
envoy, left Pristina on Friday emptyhanded after four days of
shuttle talks with the Yugoslav president, Slobodan Milosevic, and
ethnic Albanian leaders.
