   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ With all the probes into his sex
life and business dealings, Bill Clinton's influence on Capitol
Hill and with the public has been diminished. But he has not been
found guilty of any crime, and a rush to judgment can lead to a
false conclusion. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Thursday)
</P>
