   WOMEN-EDUCATION (Washington) _ Young women widened their lead
last year over young men in the numbers getting high school and
college degrees, according to a new Census Bureau report. The
report on people aged 25 to 29 says the trend has continued since
1991. By NICOLE TSONG. (Already filed; for release 12:01 a.m.
Monday, June 29)
</P>
