<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Conn., N.Y., Neb.)  (bl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   General Electric Co., Fairfield, Conn., announced plans to
provide the turbines for a $1.5 billion thermal power plant to be
built in China by a joint U.S.-Chinese venture.
</P>
<P>
   International Paper, Purchase, N.Y., agreed to acquire a
majority interest in OAO Svetogorsk, a Russian pulp and paper
business, from a Swedish packaging material concern, Tetra Laval.
Terms were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Ballantyne of Omaha Inc., Omaha, Neb., a maker of projectors and
spotlights, said it would buy back up to 1.38 million shares, or
about 10 percent of its 13.8 million shares outstanding. &QL;
</P>
