<HEADLINE>
BROOKLYN LANDLORD FACES INVESTIGATION OVER SERVICE COMPANIES 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (SUBS for photo note; no other changes)   (ART ADV.: a photo for use with this story is being sent to NYT
photo clients. Non-subscribers may make individual purchase by
calling 212 556-4204.) 
 (ps) 
 By RANDY KENNEDY    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Over the last 20 years, the families at Bedford
Gardens, a sprawling Brooklyn apartment complex, have grown
accustomed to seeing the name Kraus at every turn.
</P>
<P>
   End new lead. Pick up original 2nd graf, beginning: Their rent
checks x x x, and continue as sent.
