JOURNAL-LITHUANIA-COX, 6-26 -- Juozas Aleksiejunas, 76, in front of
a prision cell. Aleksiejunas escorts tourists around Lithuania's
KGB prison, a monument to the bleak, brutal days of the Soviet
Union. Aleksiejunas was a nationalist partisan fighter in the 1940s
who spent 4 months in the prison in central Vilnius before being
exiled to Siberia. (Charles W. Holmes/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) BEIJING -- June 26, 1998 -- CHINA-RELIGION-COX, 6-26 --
People pray outside Dong Tang, which means ``East Church.'' This is
one of China's official ``patriotic'' churches that run fairly
freely, as long as they don't talk about the Pope or any topics the
government doesn't like, such as abortion. (Joseph P. Albright/Cox
News Service Photo)
</P>
