<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, JUNE 27
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and   dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News   Service, and may need to
be adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-LANSING-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 10)
</P>
<P>
   An obituary of Marjorie Lansing, a political scientist, sent by
the New York Times News Service article on Sunday, May 10,
misstated the location of her alma mater, Florida State College for
Women. The college, now known as Florida State University, is in
Tallahassee, not Gainesville. This correction was delayed by an
editing lapse.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BOOK-TALK-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
24, about the steps that go into '`good'' publishing, misstated the
given name of the editor in chief at W.W. Norton. He is Starling
Lawrence, not Starr Lawrence.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ANTIQUES-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Thursday, June 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent Thursday, June 18,
about an auction of 20th-century art and design held on Wednesday
at the William Doyle Galleries, in Manhattan, misstated the
birthplace of the furniture designer Jens Risom. He is from
Denmark, not Sweden.
</P>
<P>
   BC-POP-LIFE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 16,
about the continuing popularity of the Japanese rock star Hide, who
died on May 2, misstated the title of his most recent No. 1 single.
It is ``Ever Free,'' not ``Stay Free.''
</P>
</TEXT>
