<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Toronto blue jays
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV, radio: TBS, 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Greg Maddux (10-2, 1.75; 1-0,
4.50 lifetime vs. Blue Jays) vs. RHP Juan Guzman (4-9, 5.44; first
appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Maddux, whose last defeat came nearly nine weeks ago, can
become the NL's first 11-game winner tonight. He is almost
completely over the stiff neck that forced him out of his last
start Monday at Yankee Stadium after just six innings. Maddux gave
up nine hits that night, more than in any of his previous 10
starts, and the three runs the Yankees scored were more than Maddux
had yielded in his previous 25 innings. Riding an eight-game win
streak, Maddux is approaching his career-best 10-game run, which he
has achieved twice, the last time June 17-Aug. 22 last season.
Guzman, coming off winter shoulder surgery for a torn labrum, has
been roughed up more than any Toronto starter. He has yielded 99
hits in 102.2 innings and already has issued an amazing 50 walks.
Maddux has walked just 16. But his 86 strikeouts are a credit to
successful surgery.
</P>
