<SLUG> BC-MACYS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Federated launches interactive division
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Federated Department Stores announced the creation of a new
interactive division, Macys.Com.
</P>
<P>
   The company said it hoped to leverage Macy's status as a leading
retailer to profit from the world of Internet commerce. Plans call
for Macys.Com to be a separate subsidiary of Federated.
</P>
<P>
   Federated maintains rather than eating away at its department
store trade, Macys.Com is designed to attract customers who don't
like department stores.
</P>
<P>
   The only other Federated store with an online outpost is
Bloomingdales (http:/www.
</P>
<P>
   bloomingdales.com). However, Macys.com president Kent Anderson
said there were no plans to include Bloomingdales.com in the
Macys.com project. Anderson also said plans call for Federated to
develop independent sites for its regional brands including Rich's
and Burdines once the Macy's site is successful.
</P>
<P>
   The current incarnation of Macys.Com offers a limited selection
of high-priced clothing, cosmetics and accessories clearly aimed at
upscale, computer-savvy shoppers. Macys.Com clearly understands the
possibilities of electronic commerce and knows what products will
appeal to its online customers (Anne Klein clothing, Clinique
cosmetics).
</P>
<P>
   They still face stiff competition from such experienced
``boutique'' shopping sites as clothiers L.L.Bean and J. Peterman;
booksellers such as Amazon.com; and computer makers such as Gateway
and Dell. Each of those online retailers has a solid knowledge of
direct marketing both on and off the Web. Macy's and Federated
don't have that.
</P>
<P>
   It's also unclear if cyber-shoppers, who like online shopping
experiences to be quick and easy, will want to browse through the
large selection and variety of offerings Macys.Com has planned.
</P>
<P>
   Anderson said a new version of Macy's online will launch in
October, with more than 2,500 items available for sale.
</P>
<P>
   Customers will be able to return or exchange merchandise at any
Macy's department store nationwide. Macys.Com also plans to
eventually offer a bilingualversion of the site.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
